
Northampton [Mass.] 20 May 1776. In Obeidiance to your Warrant dated Janry 24th1 mutilated have attended the Service of Mustering the Regiment raised in the Counties of Hampshire & Berkshire, & have inclosed the Muster-roll. Colo. Porters leaving an Officer to recruit till this Time, is the Reason why this Return has been delaydI have likewise inclosed an Accompt of my Services amounting to 6.9.4 which I pray may be paid to Mr Peter Vandervoort Mercht New York.2
